#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn2.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.30:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Nānātitthiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Various Sectarians "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Nānātitthiyasāvakasutta "
msgstr "30. The Disciples of Various Sectarians "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.66, pts2ed1.152, sc1
msgctxt "sn2.30:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn2.30:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sahali → sahalī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
#. VAR: nīko → niṅko (bj, pts1) | niko (s1-3, km, pts2)
#. VAR: vegabbhari ca → veṭambarī ca (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn2.30:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā nānātitthiyasāvakā devaputtā asamo ca sahali ca nīko ca ākoṭako ca vegabbhari ca māṇavagāmiyo ca abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ veḷuvanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, several glorious gods lit up the entire Bamboo Grove. They were Asama, Sahalī, Niṅka, Ākoṭaka, Vetambarī, and Māṇavagāmiya, and all of them were disciples of various sectarian teachers. They went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.30:1.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho asamo devaputto pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Standing to one side, the god Asama recited this verse about Pūraṇa Kassapa in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.1"
msgid "“Idha chinditamārite, "
msgstr "“In injuring and killing here, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.2"
msgid "Hatajānīsu kassapo; "
msgstr "in beating and extortion, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.3"
msgid "Na pāpaṃ samanupassati, "
msgstr "Kassapa saw no evil, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.4"
msgid "Puññaṃ vā pana attano; "
msgstr "nor any merit for oneself. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.5"
msgid "Sa ve vissāsamācikkhi, "
msgstr "What he taught should truly be trusted, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.6"
msgid "Satthā arahati mānanan”ti. "
msgstr "he’s worthy of esteem as Teacher.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn2.30:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho sahali devaputto makkhaliṃ gosālaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the god Sahalī recited this verse about Makkhali Gosala in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.153, sc4
msgctxt "sn2.30:4.1"
msgid "“Tapojigucchāya susaṃvutatto, "
msgstr "“Through mortification in disgust of sin he became well restrained. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:4.2"
msgid "Vācaṃ pahāya kalahaṃ janena; "
msgstr "He gave up arguing with people. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:4.3"
msgid "Samosavajjā virato saccavādī, "
msgstr "Refraining from false speech, he spoke the truth. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Na hi nūna tādisaṃ karoti → naha nūna tādī pakaroti (bj, s1, s2, km, pts2) | nahi nūna tādī pakaroti (s3)
msgctxt "sn2.30:4.4"
msgid "Na hi nūna tādisaṃ karoti pāpan”ti. "
msgstr "Surely such a man does no wrong!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc5
#. VAR: nāṭaputtaṃ → nātaputtaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn2.30:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho nīko devaputto nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the god Niṅka recited this verse about Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn2.30:6.1"
msgid "“Jegucchī nipako bhikkhu, "
msgstr "“Disgusted at sin, an alert mendicant, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:6.2"
msgid "Cātuyāmasusaṃvuto; "
msgstr "well restrained in the four controls; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:6.3"
msgid "Diṭṭhaṃ sutañca ācikkhaṃ, "
msgstr "explaining what is seen and heard: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:6.4"
msgid "Na hi nūna kibbisī siyā”ti. "
msgstr "surely he can be no sinner!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn2.30:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho ākoṭako devaputto nānātitthiye ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the god Ākoṭaka recited this verse about various sectarian teachers in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn2.30:8.1"
msgid "“Pakudhako kātiyāno nigaṇṭho, "
msgstr "“Pakudhaka, Kātiyāna, and Nigaṇṭha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:8.2"
msgid "Ye cāpime makkhalipūraṇāse; "
msgstr "as well as this Makkhali and Pūraṇa: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:8.3"
msgid "Gaṇassa satthāro sāmaññappattā, "
msgstr "Teachers of communities, attained ascetics, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:8.4"
msgid "Na hi nūna te sappurisehi dūre”ti. "
msgstr "surely they weren’t far from truly good men!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn2.30:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho vegabbhari devaputto ākoṭakaṃ devaputtaṃ gāthāya paccabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the god Vetambarī replied to the god Ākoṭaka in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc10
#. VAR: Sahācaritena → sahāravenāpi (si, pts2) | saha racitena (s1-3) | sagāravenāpi (pts1)
#. VAR: sigālo → siṅgālo (mr)
msgctxt "sn2.30:10.1"
msgid "“Sahācaritena chavo sigālo, "
msgstr "“Though the wretched jackal howls along, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:10.2"
msgid "Na kotthuko sīhasamo kadāci; "
msgstr "it never equals the lion. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:10.3"
msgid "Naggo musāvādī gaṇassa satthā, "
msgstr "A naked liar with suspicious conduct, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:10.4"
msgid "Saṅkassarācāro na sataṃ sarikkho”ti. "
msgstr "though they teach a community, doesn’t resemble the good.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.67, pts2ed1.154, sc11
msgctxt "sn2.30:11.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā begabbhariṃ devaputtaṃ anvāvisitvā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked took possession of the god Vetambarī and recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.1"
msgid "“Tapojigucchāya āyuttā, "
msgstr "“Those dedicated to mortification in disgust of sin, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.2"
msgid "pālayaṃ pavivekiyaṃ; "
msgstr "safeguarding their seclusion, "

# NOTE: I’m not sure what this line means, and translate following comm.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.3"
msgid "Rūpe ca ye niviṭṭhāse, "
msgstr "attached to form, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.4"
msgid "devalokābhinandino; "
msgstr "they rejoice in the heavenly realm. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.5"
msgid "Te ve sammānusāsanti, "
msgstr "Indeed, those mortals give correct instructions "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.6"
msgid "paralokāya mātiyā”ti. "
msgstr "regarding the next world.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn2.30:13.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā, māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya paccabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn2.30:14.1"
msgid "“Ye keci rūpā idha vā huraṃ vā, "
msgstr "“Whatever forms there are in this world or the world beyond, "

# NOTE: One of the clearest references to the connection between the gods and the stars.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:14.2"
msgid "Ye cantalikkhasmiṃ pabhāsavaṇṇā; "
msgstr "and those of shining beauty in the sky, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:14.3"
msgid "Sabbeva te te namucippasatthā, "
msgstr "all of these you praise, Namuci, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:14.4"
msgid "Āmisaṃva macchānaṃ vadhāya khittā”ti. "
msgstr "like bait tossed out for catching fish.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn2.30:15.1"
msgid "Atha kho māṇavagāmiyo devaputto bhagavantaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the god Māṇavagāmiya recited this verse about the Buddha in his presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn2.30:16.1"
msgid "“Vipulo rājagahīyānaṃ, "
msgstr "“Of all the mountains of Rājagaha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:16.2"
msgid "giri seṭṭho pavuccati; "
msgstr "Vipulo’s said to be the best. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:16.3"
msgid "Seto himavataṃ seṭṭho, "
msgstr "Seta is the best of the Himalayan peaks, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:16.4"
msgid "ādicco aghagāminaṃ. "
msgstr "and the sun, of travelers in space. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.156, sc17
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.1"
msgid "Samuddo udadhinaṃ seṭṭho, "
msgstr "The ocean is the best of seas, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: nakkhattānaṃva candimā → nakkhattānañca candimā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.2"
msgid "nakkhattānaṃva candimā; "
msgstr "and the moon, of lights that shine at night. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.3"
msgid "Sadevakassa lokassa, "
msgstr "But in all the world with its gods, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.4"
msgid "buddho aggo pavuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "the Buddha is declared foremost.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.5"
msgid "Nānātitthiyavaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.1"
msgid "Sivo khemo ca serī ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.2"
msgid "Ghaṭī jantu ca rohito; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.3"
msgid "Nando nandivisālo ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.4"
msgid "Susimo nānātitthiyena te dasāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.5"
msgid "Devaputtasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on Gods are complete."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
